<TITLE> North Korea appears to step away from nuclear deal </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Seoul, Sep 19 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - North Korea said on Friday it did not wish to be taken off a US terrorism blacklist, a reward it would be given if it abided by a disarmament deal, in an indication that it was stepping away from the pact. "The DPRK (North Korea) neither wishes to be delisted as a 'state sponsor of terrorism' nor expects such a thing to happen," the North's official KCNA news agency quoted a Foreign Ministry spokesman as saying
